textDelta: moscow treaty + offensive reductions + military The Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions was a treaty between the United States of America and the Russian Federation signed on May 24, 2002 in Moscow. The treaty aimed to reduce the number of deployed strategic nuclear warheads of both countries to 1,700-2,200 warheads by December 31, 2012.
